Histograms or Density plots for continuous variables

paint_data %>%
  select(R, G, B, Hue) %>%
  gather(key = "Variable", value = "Value") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Value, fill = Variable)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  facet_wrap(~Variable, scales = "free")

Condition (group) the continuous variables based on the categorical variables

paint_data %>%
  select(R, G, B, Hue, Lightness, Saturation) %>%
  gather(key = "Variable", value = "Value", -Lightness, -Saturation) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = Value, fill = Variable)) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  facet_grid(Lightness ~ Saturation + Variable, scales = "free")

Visualize the relationships between the continuous inputs

paint_data %>%
  select(R, G, B, Hue) %>%
  pairs()

Visualize the relationships between the continuous outputs

paint_data %>%
  select(R, G, B, Hue, outcome, response) %>%
  pairs()
